   resolution="reject">
   <issue_management
    owner="PDM modules"
    priority="low"
    category="representation"/>
 <description>
 <p>
   <b>SC4 part number:</b>  </p>
 <p>
   <b>(2) Clause:</b> 10303-1006
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(3) Paragraph:</b> 
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(5) Comment:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Major concept of mapped_item is missing. The entities representation_relationship_with_transformation + item_defined_transformation allows to relate shape_representations without including one into the other. However for geometric assembly mapped_item+representation map is essential.</p>
 <p>
   <b>(6) Proposal:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Add mapped_item and representation_map and make it the default for the case of geometric assembly.</p>
 </description>

<comment
   by="Tom Hendrix"
   date="04-10-08">
<description>
It was agreed at SC4 meeting in Seattle  that this issue would be closed, but that a SEDS would be placed against part 43 to add a new subtype of representation_relationship_with_transformation that specifies the direction of assembly.
</description>
</comment>
</issue>

